   "body": "<p class=\"Paragraph\">Traditional grammars refer to this mark as <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">བྱེད་སྒྲ་</span>, literally “agent-sound.” The agentive indicates the agent of the action (“by”), the instrument (“with”), the cause (“because of,” “by”), and the manner (“with”); it also marks causal subordinate clauses, in which case it may be translated by “since,” “because,” etc.</p><p class=\"Paragraph\">The agentive is formed by adding a <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ས</span> to the genitive. The variants follow the same pattern as in the case of the genitive: <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གིས་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གྱིས་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཀྱིས་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ས་</span>.</p><ul> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ས་</span> is used after vowels and <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">འ་</span></li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གིས་</span> is used after <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ག་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ང་</span></li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཀྱིས་</span> is used after <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ད་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">བ་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ས་</span> and the <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ད་དྲག་</span></li> <li><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གྱིས་</span> is used after <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ན་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མ་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ར་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ལ་</span></li> </ul><p class=\"Paragraph\">In Classical Tibetan, vowels may also be followed by the variant <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཡིས་</span>, or even by the more archaic form <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">འིས་</span>.</p><p class=\"Paragraph\">The following table gives examples of how these variants are used.</p><table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"> <tbody> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཉི་མ་</span> “Sun”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཉི་མས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">རི་མོ་</span> “Drawing”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">རི་མོས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཆུ་</span> “Water”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཆུས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མི་</span> “Man,” “person”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མིས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མེ་</span> “Fire”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མེས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མདའ་</span> “Arrow”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">མདས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">དགེ་རྒན་</span> “Teacher”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">དགེ་རྒན་གྱིས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">རྒན་ལགས་</span> “Teacher” (H)</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">རྒན་ལགས་ཀྱིས་</span></p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td width=\"151\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">དྲུང་ཡིག་</span> “Secretary”</p> </td> <td width=\"144\" valign=\"top\"> <p class=\"Paragraph\"><span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">དྲུང་ཡིག་གིས་</span></p> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table><p class=\"Paragraph\">In conversation, the three particles <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གིས་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">ཀྱིས་</span>, <span class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\">གྱིས་</span> are pronounced in exactly the same way, as an unstressed syllable: gi.</p>", 
